---
title: Method
intro: A sample page demonstrating every inline component. Open it in the Admin to see how each one is inserted, and copy the patterns into your own pages.
---

This page exists so you can see every inline component in action. Each one is inserted from the **+** menu in the body editor in the Admin.

## 1 · Callout

{% callout tone="info" title="Good to know" %}
A callout is a highlighted note. Use it for key takeaways, context, or anything that deserves emphasis without breaking the prose flow. Variants: **info**, **tip**, **warning**.
{% /callout %}

{% callout tone="warning" title="Caution" %}
The warning variant is for safety notes and contraindications.
{% /callout %}

## 2 · Pull quote

{% pullQuote attribution="Marcus Aurelius, Meditations" %}
You have power over your mind — not outside events. Realize this, and you will find strength.
{% /pullQuote %}

## 3 · Stats band

A row of big numbers for study summaries or at-a-glance metrics.

{% statsBand %}
{% stat value="78%" label="Response rate" /%}
{% stat value="n = 240" label="Cohort size" /%}
{% stat value="p < 0.01" label="Significance" /%}
{% stat value="12 wk" label="Duration" /%}
{% /statsBand %}

## 4 · Card grid

Small linked cards for "further reading" sections.

{% cardGrid %}
{% card title="The Body Keeps the Score" description="Bessel van der Kolk on trauma, memory, and the body." href="https://example.com" /%}
{% card title="Why We Sleep" description="Matthew Walker's case for sleep as the foundation of health." href="https://example.com" /%}
{% card title="The Hungry Brain" description="Stephan Guyenet on appetite regulation and obesity." href="https://example.com" /%}
{% /cardGrid %}

## 5 · Figure with caption

{% figure image="/images/figures/sample.svg" alt="Sample calibration diagram" caption="Sample figure — replace with your own uploaded image. Captions render in monospace below." /%}

## 6 · Video embed

Paste a YouTube or Vimeo URL — it renders an in-page player. The video stays hosted on YouTube/Vimeo (no bandwidth cost to you).

{% video url="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jNQXAC9IVRw" title="The first video uploaded to YouTube" /%}

## 7 · Citation

For formatted references at the end of a write-up.

{% citation authors="Doe J., Smith R." title="A representative study on the topic" source="Journal of Examples" year="2024" url="https://example.com" /%}

{% citation authors="Anonymous" title="Untitled paper without a link" source="arXiv preprint" year="2023" /%}

## 8 · Interactive tool (HTML embed)

Drop a self-contained `.html` file — like a calculator built in Claude Design — into the repo and embed it here as a responsive, auto-resizing iframe. It works on both mobile and desktop, and the height fits the tool's content automatically, so there are no inner scrollbars.

**Where the files go.** Put each tool in its own folder under `public/tools/`, with the file named `index.html`. Any images or assets the tool needs go in that same folder:

```
public/
└── tools/
    └── peptide-calculator/   (your folder name becomes the URL)
        └── index.html        (the file from Claude Design, renamed)
```

That tool is then served at `/tools/peptide-calculator/`. To add one from GitHub: open `public/tools/`, create a new folder, and upload your `.html` as `index.html`.

**How to embed it.** Insert the **Interactive tool (HTML embed)** block from the **+** menu in the body editor, then set:

- **Source path** — the folder path, with the trailing slash: `/tools/peptide-calculator/`
- **Title** — a short label (for screen-reader accessibility)
- **Minimum height** — a fallback height; the iframe grows past this to fit the content

The live example below points at the bundled sample tool at `/tools/sample/`. Resize the window or open it on a phone to see it reflow:

{% tool src="/tools/sample/" title="Sample reconstitution calculator" minHeight=300 /%}

The sample lives at `public/tools/sample/index.html` — open it to see how a self-contained tool is structured, then replace it with your own.

---

When you're done exploring, delete this page from the Admin and start writing your own.
